The paper discusses learning algorithms for probability distributions over free algebras of trees, which falls under the category of formal language theory (cs.FL). The use of algebraic representation and multiplicity tree automata suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of applications for Web Information Extraction, Web Services, and document processing suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB).
